# Rendering & Hebrew RTL

- ALL user-facing game text must be Hebrew.
- Page must use RTL layout: `<html lang="he" dir="rtl">`.
- First version: use emoji/text placeholders instead of real images.
- Final design will use image-only map clues. Support a toggle:
  `CONFIG.SHOW_HINT_LABELS_ON_MAP`
  - prototype: `true` (show emoji + label)
  - later: `false` (visual clue only)

## Answer shuffling (critical)

- Answer buttons MAY be shuffled for display.
- If shuffled, preserve the ORIGINAL option index on each button.
- On click, pass the ORIGINAL option index to game state.
- NEVER compare the shuffled display index directly to `correctIndex`.

```javascript
// ✅ keep original index when shuffling
const shuffled = shuffle(options.map((text, originalIndex) => ({ text, originalIndex })));
button.onclick = () => answer(item.originalIndex); // compare originalIndex vs correctIndex
```
